# Project Tier Policy

Defines which standards are required based on project complexity.

## Tier Definitions

### Tier A — Static/Lightweight
Examples: single-page HTML/CSS/JS sites, simple prototypes, no backend state.

### Tier B — Standard Application
Examples: typical web apps/APIs with authentication, persistence, or multiple workflows.

### Tier C — Production-Critical
Examples: multi-tenant, regulated, high-availability, or customer-critical systems.

